Subinterfaces of PathExpression in query
 interface BinaryOperation
          BinaryOperation is an operator from part of an PathExpression that gather 2 others PathExpression.
 interface Composition
          Composition takes as input two functions, f and g, such that
range(f ) = def(g), and returns a function g o f: def(f) -> range(g),
deﬁned by: (g o f )(x)= g(f(x)) for all x in def(f ).
 interface FunctionReference
          FunctionReference is a PathExpression that refers to a SchemaFunction.
 interface Pairing
          Pairing takes as input two functions f and g, such that def(f)= def(g),
and returns a function f ^ g: def(f) -> range(f) x range(g),
deﬁned by: (f ^ g)(x)= (f(x), g(x)) , for all x in def(f).
 interface Projection
          This is the usual projection function over a Cartesian product.
 interface UnaryOperation
          UnaryOperation is composed of only one operand.
